cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.NE 

This paper is about neural architecture search (NAS) for object detection, which is a computer vision task. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves reinforcement learning, which falls under cs.LG (Machine Learning), and the search for optimal architectures, which is related to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, object detection is a robotics-related task, which could be categorized under cs.RO (Robotics) and the use of deep neural networks falls under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
